text.tspan: Copy locking layer, delate key clearance on locking
and open layers, delete open keyhole on locking layer
and locking keyhole on open layer. Use non counter sunk
Copy outline and screw holes from open layer, select the outline then open path > path effects,
click plus, choose offset, set the value to 1mm, then path > object to path. Duplicte the outline
with ctrl + d, then add another offset of 3mm, then repeat object to path.
Copy outline and screw holes from case wall, delete the screw holes on case wall
as they are no longer needed, delete inner wall from case bottom
Copy layout, add an outline and screw holes (counter sunk)

Copy locking layer, open layer, case wall, and case bottom, for each one select all the parts and got to path > combine, then file > export, choose selection, choose SVG, and name each file accordingly
Arrange your keys however you like
User counter sunk screw holes for this one
